// Oravan primary lockup (brand "Version B"): the lone-O mark stands in for the
// "O", and the wordmark is cropped to "ravan" then scaled + offset on the shared
// master grid so the pair reconstructs the word "Oravan" at the wordmark's own
// proportions. The MARK is the only element that sets the size; "ravan" is
// always derived from it (RAVAN_SCALE) so the O↔ravan proportion is locked.
//
// This is the single source of truth for the Oravan logo/wordmark. Any surface
// that shows the logo/wordmark should render <OravanLockup>, sized via `markRem`
// — never resize letterforms independently. See docs/brand guidelines.
//
// Master facts (both assets are drawn in one master, so the mark's O and the
// wordmark's O are identical in master units):
//   mark viewBox     "75.7 698.5 648.9 648.9"   (648.9 square)
//   wordmark viewBox "52.3 678.2 1947.6 691.5"

